		<h2 class="display-3 center">Vocabulary to Know</h2>
		<ul class="big">
			<li>
			Fission: The nucleus of a heavy element is split causing it to release energy.
			</li>

			<li>
			Fusion: The combination of a light element's isotopes to form a heavier nuclei.
			</li>

			<li>Radiation: Radiation is any energy that is emitted. That among those included are things sucha as light, sound, and heat. When talking in terms of nuclear weapons, we describe nuclear engergy (or ionizing radiation) as radiation.</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Alpha Radiation: Radiation of a helium nuclei.</li>
				<li>Beta Radiation: Radiation of electrons or positrons emitted from atoms at speeds close to the speed of light.</li>
				<li>Gamma Radiation: Electromagnetic waves released while radioactive decay takes place.</li>
			</ul>

			<li>Chain Reaction: The process of nuclear fission in which the neutrons released trigger other nuclear fission reactions at an equivelant or greator rate</li>
			<li>Critical Mass: The amount of a fissile substance that can have a self-sustaining chain reaction.</li>
		</ul>
