		<h3 class="center">Atom Bomb</h3>
		<p class="center">A nuclear bomb whose energy comes from the fission of uranium or plutonium. A fission reaction takes place within the bomb in order to release a lot of energy at one time.</p>
		<img style="padding-bottom: 25px;padding-top:35px;display: block;width: 300px;" src="http://www.viewzone.com/hbomb.mk41.jpg" class="image-rounded ocenter animated infinite shake tada">
		<h3 class="center">Hydrogen Bomb</h3>
		<p class="center">A nuclear weapon that derives its energy from hydrogen undergoing fusion. It is commonly refered to as a thermonuclear weapon. Hydrogen bombs undergo a fusion reaction in order to release energy. These bombs are 10-100 times as explosive as their atomic bomb counterparts</p>
